    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">11, York Place, | Portman Square, | London. W.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>1 March 1872</date>
                    <salute>Dear M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Darwin</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>As you know that I rather pride myself on being systematic—I was annoyed today that I could not at once lay my hands on the analyses of chalk, I found them the moment you left<ref target="#foot.f1"/>—the difficulty in doing so before being because I had entered them under the head of investigations of the Atlantic mud<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>I enclose herewith the results of 2 analyses which you can take as representatives only to show the components of the true chalk which contains the flints—and of the most impure or grey chalk (chalk marl)—lowest in the series</p>
<p>Yours very truly | David Forbes</p> 
<table> 
<row><cell cols="3" rend="left">White chalk– with flints</cell></row>
    <row><cell/><cell/><cell rend="centre">Shoreham</cell></row>
    <row><cell/><cell/><cell>Carbonate of Lime –</cell> <cell rend="right">98·40</cell></row>
    <row><cell/><cell/><cell>    —     of Magnesia</cell> <cell rend="right">0·08</cell></row>
    <row><cell/><cell/><cell>Insoluble (silicious rock debris)</cell> <cell rend="right">1·10</cell></row>
    <row><cell/><cell/><cell>Alumina(with Phosporic acid</cell> <cell rend="right borderBottom">0·42</cell></row>
    <row><cell/><cell/><cell/><cell rend="right">100·00</cell> </row>
    <row><cell/></row>
    <row><cell cols="3">Grey chalk. beds resting on greensand</cell></row>
<row><cell cols="3">level of low water Folkestone</cell></row>
    <row><cell/><cell/><cell>Carbonate of lime</cell> <cell rend="right">94·09</cell></row>
    <row><cell/><cell/><cell>    —     of Magnesium</cell> <cell rend="right">0·31</cell></row>
    <row><cell/><cell/><cell>Insoluble (rock debris)</cell> <cell rend="right">3·61</cell></row>
    <row><cell/><cell/><cell>Phosphoric acid</cell> <cell rend="right">traces</cell> </row>
    <row><cell rend="right">Sea</cell> <cell rows="2"><hi rend="stretchyVertical">}</hi></cell><cell>Chloride of sodium</cell> <cell rend="right">1·29</cell></row>
    <row><cell rend="right">infiltration</cell> </row>
    <row><cell/><cell/><cell>Water</cell> <cell rend="right borderBottom">0·70</cell></row>
    <row><cell/><cell/><cell/> <cell rend="right">100·00</cell></row> </table>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="annotations">
                <note><hi rend="italic">Top of letter</hi>: ‘Worms’<ref target="#foot.f3"/><hi rend="italic">red crayon</hi></note>
            </div>

            
            
            
