        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8216.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to W. E. Darwin, [1 March 1872]</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">Forbes analysed chalk samples in order to compare them with samples of Atlantic mud collected on the <hi rend="italic">Lightning</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Porcupine</hi> expeditions (see <hi rend="italic">Quarterly Journal of the Geological Society</hi> 27 (1871): xlviii–xlix n., and Thomson 1873, pp. 467 ff.).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">CD cited the results of Forbes’s analysis of chalk in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2241.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Earthworms</hi></ref>, pp. 299–300.</note>
        </div>        
            
